<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p>To make your Word source document more useful for online output, it is broken up into smaller elements called "topics," which are based on the heading styles in the document. After you create a Doc-To-Help project and build some output from it, Doc-To-Help automatically creates multiple topics as a result, structuring the content for online documentation. Heading 1 styles in your Word document automatically become parent topics, and all of the Heading 2 styles under a Heading 1 style become subtopics. Just keep in mind that these topics are not created until you build at least one target in your project.</p>
        <p>The Topics window pane displays all of the topics that were created as a result of the most recent build. There are several tasks you can perform in this window.</p>
        <p>
            <img src="../../../../Images/D2H/Interface/Window-Panes/Topics-Window-Pane.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
        </p>
        <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="D2H-Guides.D2H-Touring-Workspace-Guide" />
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>Drag-and-Drop</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p>From this window, you can select topics that can be dragged and dropped into the Contents, Index and Groups, or Related Topics panes. You can also drag topics into source documents to create links.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only,Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Nav-Links/Drag-Drop-Linking.htm">Drag-and-Drop Linking</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only,Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Nav-Links/Drag-Drop-Linking.htm">Drag-and-Drop Linking</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="D2H-Guides.D2H-Touring-Workspace-Guide"> See the online Help or the <span class="EmphasisItalic">Documents, Templates, and Content Guide</span>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                <p class="note" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: Black;&quot; class=&quot;mcFormatColor&quot;&gt;Note: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;">You can also drag and drop topics from the Contents panel in the Doc-To-Help Project panel to create links in your source documents.</p>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>Right-Click</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p>You can right-click in the Topics panel and select several options, including the following:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Open Topic </span>Open the source document and highlight the heading where the topic starts.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Show Filter Row </span>Show/hide the filter row.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Clear Filter </span>Clear the filter.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Show Deleted Topics </span>Show/hide deleted topics.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Purge Deleted Topics </span>Purge deleted topics.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Default Topic </span>Specify a topic as the default for the project (the first displayed in the online output).</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Remove Sort</span> This will remove the option to sort the contents of a selected column alphabetically.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Reset Column Layout </span>Return to the default column display.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Columns </span>Specify the columns to display.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Copy </span>Copy the selected row(s) in the Topics window.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Paste </span>Paste the copied rows to the selected location in the Topics window.</li>
                    <li><span class="SetOffFirstLevel">Properties </span>Open the Topic Properties dialog, which lets you choose various settings for the topic. This includes the ability to apply platform, target, or attribute conditions to topics.<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only,Snippets.Snippet1"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Conditions/Conditions.htm">About Conditions</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only,Snippets.Snippet2"> See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Legacy-HTML5/Conditions/About-Conditions-D2H.htm">About Conditions</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="D2H-Guides.D2H-Touring-Workspace-Guide"> See the online Help or the <span class="EmphasisItalic">Documents, Templates, and Content Guide</span>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
                </ul>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>Arrange Columns and Sort Information</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p>Columns may be rearranged by selecting the column header and dragging to the desired position. Click on a column header to sort by that column.</p>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../../Shared/All/Print-Output/Empty-Page-Break-After.flsnp" MadCap:conditions="D2H-Guides.D2H-Touring-Workspace-Guide" />
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>Linking to Deleted Topics</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p>
                    <MadCap:snippetText src="../../Topics/Deleted-Topics-Identified1.flsnp" /> Furthermore, in the Link dialog, you can create links to such a deleted topic without first rebuilding a target that is conditioned to include it.</p>
                <MadCap:snippetBlock src="../../Topics/Deleted-Topics-Identified2.flsnp" />
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
        <MadCap:pageBreak MadCap:conditions="D2H-Guides.D2H-Touring-Workspace-Guide" />
        <MadCap:dropDown>
            <MadCap:dropDownHead>
                <MadCap:dropDownHotspot>Rename Topic URLs</MadCap:dropDownHotspot>
            </MadCap:dropDownHead>
            <MadCap:dropDownBody>
                <p>A URL column is available in the Topics Panel. This column shows the URL used for each topic in the grid. You can change the URL for a particular topic if you want.</p>
                <ol>
                    <li>Double-click in the cell showing the topic URL.</li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Type the new URL, but keep .htm at the end.</p>
                        <p>
                            <img src="../../../../Images/D2H/Interface/Window-Panes/Rename-Topic-URL.png" alt="" title="" class="MaxWidth100Percent" />
                        </p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
                <div class="note">
                    <p class="Note-Text">You can also manually change the generated URL for a topic in the Topic Properties dialog. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="General.Online-Only">See <MadCap:xref href="../../../../../D2H/Topics/Setting-D2HML-Topic-Properties.htm">Setting D2HML Topic Properties</MadCap:xref>.</MadCap:conditionalText></p>
                </div>
            </MadCap:dropDownBody>
        </MadCap:dropDown>
    </body>
</html>